**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- DNS resolution occurs twice: once during validation, once during HTTP request
- Attacker controls DNS TTL and can return different IPs on subsequent queries
- AWS/GCP/Azure metadata endpoints become accessible, exposing IAM credentials
- Internal services behind the firewall become accessible to attackers

