Validating hostnames at request time is dangerously insufficient due to DNS rebinding attacks. An attacker can set up a DNS server that returns a safe IP during your validation check, then switches to an internal IP (like 169.254.169.254 for AWS metadata) when your application actually makes the connection.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```java
