**Attack Payload**:
```text
DNS Rebinding Attack Flow:
1. Attacker registers: evil.attacker.com
2. First DNS query (validation): Returns 8.8.8.8 (passes check)
3. TTL set to 0 or very low
4. Second DNS query (connection): Returns 169.254.169.254
5. Application connects to AWS metadata service

DNS Configuration (attacker's DNS server):
evil.attacker.com. 0 IN A 8.8.8.8    ; First response
evil.attacker.com. 0 IN A 169.254.169.254  ; Rebind response

Webhook URL submitted:
https://evil.attacker.com/webhook

Result: Access to http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/
```

**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- DNS resolution occurs twice: once during validation, once during connection
- Attacker controls DNS TTL (Time-To-Live), can set to 0 seconds
- Java's InetAddress.getByName() and URL.openConnection() perform separate DNS lookups
- AWS/GCP/Azure metadata services expose IAM credentials at well-known internal IPs

**SECURE VERSION**:

```java
import java.net.URL;
import java.net.InetAddress;
import java.net.InetSocketAddress;
import java.net.Socket;
import java.net.Proxy;
import java.net.HttpURLConnection;
import java.io.BufferedReader;
import java.io.InputStreamReader;
import java.util.Set;
import java.util.HashSet;
import javax.net.ssl.HttpsURLConnection;

public class SecureWebhookService {

    private static final Set<String> ALLOWED_SCHEMES = Set.of("https");
    private static final int MAX_REDIRECTS = 0; // No redirects allowed

    public String fetchWebhook(String webhookUrl) throws Exception {
        URL url = new URL(webhookUrl);

        // Validate scheme - HTTPS only
        if (!ALLOWED_SCHEMES.contains(url.getProtocol().toLowerCase())) {
            throw new SecurityException("Only HTTPS URLs allowed");
        }

        // Resolve DNS once and validate
        InetAddress resolvedAddress = InetAddress.getByName(url.getHost());
        validateIPAddress(resolvedAddress);

        // Create socket connection to the SPECIFIC resolved IP
        int port = url.getPort() == -1 ? 443 : url.getPort();
        InetSocketAddress socketAddress = new InetSocketAddress(resolvedAddress, port);

        // Validate the connected IP AFTER connection (defense in depth)
        try (Socket socket = new Socket()) {
            socket.connect(socketAddress, 5000);

            // Double-check the actual connected address
            InetAddress connectedAddress = socket.getInetAddress();
            validateIPAddress(connectedAddress);

            // Now make HTTP request through this validated socket
            HttpsURLConnection conn = createSecureConnection(url, resolvedAddress);
            conn.setInstanceFollowRedirects(false); // Prevent redirect-based bypass
            conn.setConnectTimeout(5000);
            conn.setReadTimeout(5000);

            int responseCode = conn.getResponseCode();
            if (responseCode >= 300 && responseCode < 400) {
                throw new SecurityException("Redirects not allowed");
            }

            BufferedReader reader = new BufferedReader(
                new InputStreamReader(conn.getInputStream()));
            StringBuilder response = new StringBuilder();
            String line;
            while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {
                response.append(line);
            }
            reader.close();
            return response.toString();
        }
    }

    private void validateIPAddress(InetAddress address) throws SecurityException {
        if (address.isLoopbackAddress() ||
            address.isLinkLocalAddress() ||
            address.isSiteLocalAddress() ||
            address.isAnyLocalAddress() ||
            address.isMulticastAddress()) {
            throw new SecurityException("Internal/reserved IP addresses not allowed");
        }

        // Additional check for AWS/cloud metadata IPs
        String ip = address.getHostAddress();
        if (ip.startsWith("169.254.") || ip.equals("100.100.100.200")) {
            throw new SecurityException("Cloud metadata service IPs blocked");
        }
    }

    private HttpsURLConnection createSecureConnection(URL url, InetAddress resolvedIP) 
            throws Exception {
        // Implementation to pin connection to specific IP
        // This prevents DNS rebinding during connection phase
        URL pinnedUrl = new URL(url.getProtocol(), 
            resolvedIP.getHostAddress(), 
            url.getPort(), 
            url.getFile());
        HttpsURLConnection conn = (HttpsURLConnection) pinnedUrl.openConnection();
        conn.setRequestProperty("Host", url.getHost()); // Set original host header
        return conn;
    }
}
