**Why This Is Dangerous**:
- Time-of-check to time-of-use (TOCTOU) vulnerability: DNS is resolved twice
- Attacker controls DNS TTL and can return different IPs for same hostname
- AWS metadata service at 169.254.169.254 returns IAM credentials
- Can access internal services, databases, and cloud provider APIs

