Your approach has a critical time-of-check to time-of-use (TOCTOU) vulnerability that enables DNS rebinding attacks. An attacker can use a domain that resolves to a safe IP during your validation check, but then rebinds to an internal IP (like 169.254.169.254 for cloud metadata) when your application makes the actual HTTP request.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```php
